    "creditline": "Gift of Lella and Massimo Vignelli",
    "description": "On an orange-red ground, paragraphs of black text in upper left. Title in black, upper right: Third Thursday: \/ The Business of Design. Under this are registers in white with black text with information. Lower section has grid pattern in white with what looks like a 3D structure in shape of a dollar sign [$].",
    "justification": null,
    "gallery_text": "Graphic designers Michael Bierut and Massimo Vignelli collaborated on the design of this poster while working at Vignelli Associates. The International Center for Design New York (IDCNY) hired the studio to create material to promote its series of seminars on \u201cthe business of design,\u201d which gives this poster its title. Vignelli viewed graphic design as a way of organizing information,  so the hierarchy of type, with respect to size and weight of the letterforms, is clearly delimited. He was also known to use only a handful of clean and modern typefaces on any given project, upholding his idea that typefaces should be objective; for Vignelli, the role of typography was to effectively communicate the concept of a work.  In The Business of Design, created in 1988, the layout is organized on a grid, as is customary with Vignelli\u2019s printed matter, and the graphic dollar sign is a composition of lines, angles, and shading, making the image appear to recede into the page.",
